1993 sexually transmitted diseases treatment guidelines. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention. These guidelines for the treatment of patients with sexually transmitted diseases (STDs) were developed by staff members of CDC after consultation with a group of invited experts who met in Atlanta on January 19-21, 1993. Included are new recommendations for single-dose oral therapy for gonococcal infections, chlamydial infections, and chancroid new regimens for the treatment of bacterial vaginosis (BV) and outpatient management of pelvic inflammatory disease (PID)